gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 135, Bucks 95
gameRecap.excerpt: Cleveland snaps a three-game win streak as they defeat Milwaukee, 135-95, and win their sixth consecutive game to improve to 24-15. Georges Niang led the Cavaliers with a career-high 33 points (13-14 FG, season-high five 3PT), along with five rebounds as Donovan Mitchell (31 points, five rebounds, seven assists) and Jarrett Allen (21 points, 13 rebounds) totaled 52 points. Damian Lillard led five Bucks players in double-figures with 17 points and five assists. Milwaukee moves to 28-13 on the year.
